Peru Bank Loans Rise 20 Percent in August, Association Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-09-19T17:25:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/peru-bank-loans-rise-20-percent-in-august-association-says.html
Peru’s outstanding bank loans rose
20 percent as of Aug. 31, compared with a year earlier, the
Andean country’s banking association Asbanc said.  Outstanding loans totaled 122 billion soles ($44.5 billion)
last month,  Asbanc  said in an e-mailed statement. Loans rose 0.5
percent from July. The loan delinquency rate fell 19 basis
points, or 0.19 percentage point, to 1.57 percent in August from
a year earlier, Asbanc said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  